<h1>About This Project</h1>

<p>
  This is a <strong>Rails Intro Project</strong> that demonstrates key concepts of **ActiveRecord, API integration, pagination, and filtering**.
  The project sources its data from two primary sources:
</p>

<h2>📌 Data Sources</h2>

<ul>
  <li>💾 <strong>Faker</strong>: Used for generating **fake Star Wars characters**, including names, species, birth year, and gender.</li>
  <li>🌐 <strong>SWAPI API</strong>: The <a href="https://swapi.dev/" target="_blank">Star Wars API</a> provides real character and film data, including:
    <ul>
      <li>Character Names, Species, Birth Year, Gender</li>
      <li>Film Titles, Episode Numbers, and Release Dates</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>📊 Database Structure</h2>

<p>
  The database consists of three main tables:
</p>

<table border="1" cellpadding="8">
  <tr>
    <th>Table</th>
    <th>Description</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>characters</strong></td>
    <td>Stores **Star Wars characters**, their species, birth year, gender, and geographic location (latitude & longitude).</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>films</strong></td>
    <td>Stores **Star Wars films**, including title, episode number, and release date.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>appearances</strong></td>
    <td>A **join table** that records **which characters appeared in which films**.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<h2>🔗 ActiveRecord Associations</h2>
<p>The project includes **4 ActiveRecord associations**:</p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="8">
  <tr>
    <th>Model</th>
    <th>Association</th>
    <th>Type</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Character</td>
    <td>has_many :appearances</td>
    <td>One-to-Many</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Character</td>
    <td>has_many :films, through: :appearances</td>
    <td>Many-to-Many</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Film</td>
    <td>has_many :appearances</td>
    <td>One-to-Many</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Film</td>
    <td>has_many :characters, through: :appearances</td>
    <td>Many-to-Many</td>
  </tr>
</table>
